post.name: Studies in Communication, Culture, Information and Technology
Studies in Communication, Culture, Information and Technology

cmCourseInfo.description: This course examines different information and communication technologies (ICTs) through the analysis of such genres as contemporary written, visual, oral, electronic and musical forms. It illustrates a range of theoretical perspectives that seek to explain the relationship between communication and technology. This course will also examine, briefly, the history of ICTs. [24L, 11P]
cmCourseInfo.title: Contemporary Communication Technologies

Enrolment Controls
P Priority

Some students are given priority access until a specific date.  See the enrolment controls information for which students may enrol as of the current date. 

Unless specific course notes indicate otherwise, enrolment in Priority courses will open as of:

  • Wednesday, March 1 to all students registered in Arts and Science and Daniels who are specified in the priority enrolment controls shown;
  • Monday, March 6th to any additional Arts and Science and Daniels students who were not specified in the first set of priority enrolment controls;
  • Tuesday, April 11th to students registered in other St. George Campus undergraduate faculties; and,
  • Wednesday, April 12th to students registered with University of Toronto Mississauga and University of Toronto Scarborough.
E Enrol through Daniels' Registrar's Office Enrolment not available via ACORN.  Enrolment details/deadlines can be found in course notes.
R Restricted Course/section is restricted at all times to students specified in the enrolment controls.
